The paper deals with image manipulation and understanding, specifically in the areas of segmentation, object pasting, and object removal. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel generative model for this purpose, which involves adversarial training and cycle consistency losses, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of bounding box supervision, which suggests a possible connection to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
